Cosatu is expected to outline the outcomes of the Central Executive Committee meeting. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The union federation Cosatu will hold a media briefing following their three-day Central Executive Committee meeting. Cosatu is expected to outline the outcomes of the meeting. On Wednesday, Finance Minister, Tito Mboweni, announced the public sector wage will be cut by a R160-billion to balance the books. Cosatu says government's plan to cut the public sector wage bill means war.